title: Appointments to Committee on Financial Assistance for Family Members of those who Sacrifice their Lives to Save Others
content_text:
p>
The Government today (February 2) announced the appointment of three new members 
and the re-appointment of one incumbent member to the Committee on Financial 
Assistance for Family Members of those who Sacrifice their Lives to Save Others 
for a term of two years. The appointments will take effect from February 11 this 
year. The new members appointed are: Mr Lee Jark-pui, Mr Ng Sze-fuk and Miss Gabriella 
Wong Siu-ling. Mr Lee has extensive public service experience and has served on

Wong Siu-ling. Mr Lee has extensive public service experience and has served on 
different boards and advisory bodies. Mr Ng, who also has rich experience in 
public service, is the Chairman of the Sai Kung District Council. Miss Wong is 
the Agency Director of the Hong Kong Children and Youth Services. She is also 
serving on boards and committees relating to social welfare. The incumbent member who has been re-appointed is Mr Poon Siu-ping. The Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food, Dr York Chow, welcomed the

appointments of the three new members and the re-appointment of the incumbent 
member. He looked forward to their contribution to the committee. Dr Chow also thanked the outgoing members, Mr Chau How-chen and Mrs Justina 
Leung Ngai Mou-yin, for their contribution to the work of the committee during 
their term of appointment. The committee serves as the approving authority to assess and determine 
applications under the financial assistance scheme to family members of an 
individual who dies as a result of trying to save or protect others. The scheme

individual who dies as a result of trying to save or protect others. The scheme represents the Government's recognition of the honourable sacrifice of the deceased individual and assistance to alleviate the financial hardship that the surviving family members may face as a consequence of the heroic act.
